2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE BILL NO. 102
BY SENATOR PRESSLY
1 AN ACT
2 To enact R.S. 32:1253.1, relative to the Louisiana Motor Vehicle Commission Law; to
3 provide for a private right of action for trade associations; to provide for standing
4 and remedies; to provide for an effective date; and to provide for related matters.
5 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
6 Section 1. R.S. 32:1253.1 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
7 §1253.1. Private right of action; association standing
8 A. A trade association may bring an action or intervene in an action in
9 its own name or on behalf of one or more of its members as provided in
10 Subsection B of this Section, if it meets all of the following conditions:
11 (1) It is primarily comprised of and controlled by a minimum of one
12 hundred licensed motor vehicle dealers.
13 (2) A minimum of one of its members holds a valid license under this
14 Chapter and has standing to sue or intervene individually.
15 (3) The interests the association seeks to protect are germane to its
16 purpose.
17 (4) Neither the claim asserted nor the relief requested requires the
18 participation of individual members.
19 B. A trade association prevailing pursuant to this Section may be granted
20 any of the following remedies:
21 (1) Declaratory relief.
22 (2) Injunctive relief.
23 (3) Reasonable costs and attorney fees.
24 C. An action by a trade association pursuant to this Section may be
25 brought before the commission or in any district court of competent
26 jurisdiction.
